quran[7]{c,v,t,f}:
  6,95,"Indeed, Allah is the Splitter of the grain and the fruit stone. He brings out the living from the dead{1}, and<i class=""s"">(He is) </i>the Bringer Out of the dead from the living{2}. Such is Allah, so how can you<a class=""sup""><sup>pl </sup></a>be averted<i class=""s"">(from the truth) </i>?",footnotes:1:A grammatical shift in Arabic from a nominal sentence to a verbal sentence.A grammatical shift in Arabic from a verbal sentence to a nominal sentence.
  6,96,"<i class=""s"">(He is) </i>the Splitter of the daybreak, and <span class=""h"">He has made<sup foot_note=""80007"" class=""qiraat"">1</sup> </span>the night for rest and the sun and the moon for calculation; such is the determining of the Almighty, the All-Knowing."
  6,97,"And it is He Who made for you the stars, that you may be guided by them in the darkness<i class=""s"">(es) </i>of land and sea. Surely, We{1}have detailed the signs for people who know.",footnotes:1:A grammatical shift from 3rd person to 1st person.
  6,98,"And it is He Who initiated you from a single self, then <span class=""h"">a place of settlement<sup foot_note=""80009"" class=""qiraat"">1</sup> </span><span class=""h"">and a storage</span>. Surely, We<a class=""sup""><sup>a </sup></a>have detailed the signs for people who comprehend."
  6,99,"And it is He who sent down water from the sky, and with it We<a class=""sup""><sup>a </sup></a>brought out the germination of everything, then We brought out from it greenery from which We bring out{1}layered grain. And out of the palm-trees—from their spathes— clusters of dates, hanging low, and gardens of grapevines, and the olives, and the pomegranates—similar{2}yet dissimilar{3}. Look at its produce when it has yielded its produce and<i class=""s"">(look at) </i>its ripening. Most surely in that are signs for people who believe.",footnotes:1:A grammatical shift from past tense to present tense.In kind.In taste.
  6,100,"Yet they made for Allah associates—the unseen beings{1}—although He created them, and <span class=""h"">they invented<sup foot_note=""80014"" class=""qiraat"">2</sup> </span>for Him sons and daughters, without<i class=""s"">(any) </i>knowledge. Highly Exalted is He and Most High, far above what they describe.",footnotes:1:The Arabic word used is jinnwhich are unseen beings that are accountable for their actions.
  6,101,"Originator of the heavens and the earth—how can He have offspring when He never had a consort? And He created everything, and He is All-Knowing of everything."
